me per formula unit. The transition pressures to these phases are\ndetermined and for LiGaO2 found to be in good agreement with experimental\nstudies. The $R\\bar{3}m$phase also has a comparably high but slightly indirect\nband gap while the rocksalt type phase if found to have a considerably smaller\ngap of about 3.1 eV in LiGaO2 and 1.0 eV in NaGaO2.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Oct 2020 20:49:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-13"}
